<div id="main">

<p class="lq">Rebecca [Solomon] became a draftsman on wood, illustrator, assistant to her brother <a href="../../../painting/solomona/index.html">Abraham</a>, copyist for <a href="../../../painting/millais/index.html">John Everett Millais</a>, and exhibited her own oils and watercolors at the Royal Academy and other venues. —  Comment on <span class="lqpainting">The Friend in Need</span> on the Met Museum website.</p>


<a href="1.html"><img src="1.jpg" height="200" class="floatright"/></a>

